Proposal three provides minimal benefits to groups apple-🍎 and bee-🐝, while giving a moderate benefit to group cow-🐮. This proposal also favors one group over the others.

Considering the goal of finding the best compromise, proposal two appears to be the most balanced option. It provides substantial benefits to all three groups, even though the benefits are not entirely equal. By choosing proposal two, each group receives a significant improvement, and no group is left with minimal benefits.

Proposal two heavily favors group cow-🐮 with an 82-year increase, but offers very little (only 1 year) to the other two groups. This skewed distribution makes it a less balanced compromise.

Proposal three benefits groups apple-🍎 and bee-🐝 reasonably well with 14 and 18-year increases, but leaves group cow-🐮 with only a 1-year gain. The total area is also significantly lower than proposal one.

Considering all factors, proposal one seems to strike the best balance by providing notable benefits to all groups, resulting in the greatest total positive impact. It is the most equitable compromise given the situation.

Therefore, my answer is (A) Proposal one.
